    "body": "As it currently stands, we have a limited number of bounce buffers (i.e. `spark.rapids.shuffle.ucx.bounceBuffers.*.count`). If we have more more outstanding messages than bounce buffers, messages will likely wait. Especially if the message size is smaller than a bounce buffer configured size (`spark.rapids.shuffle.ucx.bounceBuffers.size`).\r\n\r\nWe think using an allocator on top of the bounce buffer poll will help with this situation, and make it easier to configure (we'd remove the \"count\" setting, and there would be a \"max allocation\" setting instead). ",
